title: For Sale/Trade:  Harton/Fishpaw Custom Old Model Ruger Super Blackhawk
postcontent: I traded into this last year, mainly because of the Roy Fishpaw Dall Sheep Horn grips. It's an Old Model Super Blackhawk 44 mag that has been to Alan Harton. He cut the barrel down to 5 1/2", and added his front sight and a Bowen rear sight. He installed a steel ejector rod housing, fit the gripframe and grips to the gun, and polished and re-blued the gun. I have the invoice. I'm not unhappy with this gun. I'll probably just never shoot it. I've got the itch for something new, and thought I'd see if someone with an appreciation of what it is might be interested. Now, for the rationalizing. The last Harton invoice was about $750. The Fishpaw grips would probably cost $800 to reproduce, if Fishpaw were still taking new orders. So at $1500, you're getting the base gun free. I'd really rather trade for a TRP/Dan Wesson/Les Baer-type 1911, but single action revolver guys sometimes aren't 1911 guys. Maybe an interesting levergun plus cash. Or maybe an OM Flattop Ruger or OM 357 Ruger Blackhawk 44 special conversion plus cash. Or a Colt SAA. You kind-of see what would interest me.I'd even consider selling the grips and gripframe for $750. title: For Sale/Trade:  SIG Sauer P238 w/Extras
postcontent:
For sale or trade we have a lovely little SIG Sauer P238, widely regarded as the world's finest .380 ACP pistol. This one is in great shape, having spent most of its life in my gun safe except for test firing of about 100 rounds, in which it was found to be totally reliable with not only full metal jacket ammo, but with defense hollowpoints as well. This beautiful pocket gun is extremely accurate, with excellent tritium night sights and a great trigger. This would make an exceptionally good gun for small statured people, those with smaller hands, or those with hand strength issues, because the slide is quite easy to pull back, the trigger is short and light, and the gun only weighs 15 ounces. While the .380 cartridge is reasonably powerful (about the same as a .38 Special), recoil is light. This would also be a great self-defense gun for a professional person who needs to carry in complete concealment and never let anyone know they were armed, because it is so small and light, but still easy to hit with.
This P238 comes with everything it had when it was new, including the box, papers, lock, factory belt holster and manual, but there have also been some things added. In addition to the factory Rosewood grips, there is a set of custom Hogue rubber grips, with unusual SIG medallions added to them, an additional 7 round factory magazine for a total of 3 magazines (these cost $45) and a DeSantis Nemesis pocket holster. So, truly, in this package, you would get everything you need for daily carry. I even have some .380 practice ammo and some Gold Dot hollowpoints I can sell with the gun, although they are NOT included in the price.
Since this is my personal firearm, I'm willing to consider trades on high quality handguns mostly. I like 1911's, Glocks, and classic Smith and Wesson revolvers, but if you have something else to trade, let me hear about it. I teach firearms classes and do gun writing, so you never know what I might be interested in.
Transactions will take place at my office in Homestead. You'll need a Florida Driver's License and I will issue a Bill of Sale. Please email me with any questions.
 
Thanks for looking at my listing!
